\code{pq_to_tidy()} is the canonical phyloseq-to-tidy data-preparation module for
the pqverse. It owns the full pipeline: cleaning, flattening, optional
sample aggregation, optional abundance transformation, and fact/bifactor
resolution. Every ggplotpq plot function calls \code{pq_to_tidy()} instead of
reinventing its own data-prep pipeline.

The function builds the tidy tibble from scratch using \code{tidyr::pivot_longer()}
(it does not wrap \code{phyloseq::psmelt()}). Taxonomic rank grouping happens in
tibble space (no \code{tax_glom()}). Sample aggregation happens in tibble space
(no \code{merge_samples()} round-trip).

\strong{Alternative transform approaches:} users may also transform the phyloseq
object before calling \code{pq_to_tidy()} via \code{MiscMetabar::transform_pq()}, or
transform the tibble after via tidyverse \code{mutate()} (e.g.
\code{dplyr::mutate(abundance = abundance / sum(abundance))}).
}
